# JMeter Load Test Script Runbook (Four Monolith Applications)

## 0. Always restart the corresponding Docker images before each run

1. Stop and restart the corresponding monolith application containers (AcmeAir / JPetStore / DayTrader / Plants) to ensure a clean state.
2. Wait until the application is fully started (homepage is accessible), then run the JMeter scripts.

# Enter the directory that contains docker-compose.yml
cd .\docker

# Stop and remove all containers
docker compose down

# Start all services (run in background)
docker compose up -d

# Check status
docker compose ps

# View logs for a single container (e.g., JPetStore)
docker logs jpetstore

## 1. Prerequisites

1. JMeter 5.6.3 is installed, and `$env:JMETER_HOME` points to that installation.
2. The current working directory is the repository root.
3. The JMeter test plans (.jmx) in this repository are archived under: `scripts\jmeter\`.
4. In each `.jmx`, ensure the target URL and local ports match your environment (e.g., JPetStore uses `http://localhost:8083/jpetstore`).

## 2. Run the four JMeter scripts in PowerShell

Run the following commands **in PowerShell** in order (note: use backtick ` as the line continuation character).

> Tip: set `$JMETER_HOME` to your local JMeter install and run these commands from the repository root.

### 2.1 JPetStore

```powershell
& "$env:JMETER_HOME\bin\jmeter.bat" -n `
  -t "scripts\jmeter\jpetstore.jmx" `
  -l "results\jmeter\jpetstore_results.jtl" `
  -j "results\jmeter\jpetstore_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.2 Plants

```powershell
& "$env:JMETER_HOME\bin\jmeter.bat" -n `
  -t "scripts\jmeter\plants.jmx" `
  -l "results\jmeter\plants_results.jtl" `
  -j "results\jmeter\plants_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.3 DayTrader

```powershell
& "$env:JMETER_HOME\bin\jmeter.bat" -n `
  -t "scripts\jmeter\daytrader.jmx" `
  -l "results\jmeter\daytrader_results.jtl" `
  -j "results\jmeter\daytrader_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.4 AcmeAir

```powershell
& "$env:JMETER_HOME\bin\jmeter.bat" -n `
  -t "scripts\jmeter\acmeair.jmx" `
  -l "results\jmeter\acmeair_results.jtl" `
  -j "results\jmeter\acmeair_jmeter.log" `

```

## 3. Output file conventions

- JTL: `results/jmeter/<system>_results.jtl`
- JMeter log: `results/jmeter/<system>_jmeter.log`
- HTML report: `results/jmeter/<system>_html_report/`

Where `<system>` is one of `acmeair`, `jpetstore`, `daytrader`, or `plants`.
